node.text:
Artisans at work at Distileria @Teremana building more handmade Copper Pot Stills. It is quite special to have a process that uses 100% handmade copper pot stills which date back to traditional tequila making and gives Teremana tequila its unique flavor profile. I guess while we’re at it we can also add that we love drinking a tequila that was crafted by the brand selling it and not just purchased from someone else and bottled…Pay attention to those NOM numbers…👍🏻 

#tequila #agave #howitsmade

Our friends at @volcantequila & @middletonmixology crafted a very exclusive Volcan version of the SmokeTop🔥 We were at @tocamadera when @charitykjohnston created the first cocktail using the new SmokeTop and as you can see it is visually stunning! 💯 Volcan Tequila harvests their agave in the shadow of a volcano and now your cocktail can be smoked in the shadow of a volcano as well…🌋🍹
(Drink Recipe Below)

🎥: Shot and edited by @aj_sjostrom for Licensed To Distill®
📸: Cover photo by @spiritandspoon 

“De la Tierra” by @charitykjohnston
2oz @volcantequila Cristalino
1oz epazote, bell pepper & mango purée 
1oz lemon 
.5oz Campari 
.5oz Amaro

We recently selected a few bartenders and sent them a bottle of @blackenedamericanwhiskey and a @gopro and asked them to give us a look into a cocktail they are enjoying at home! @blackstraprob from @strongwateranaheim went with his “Black Rose”🌹🥃 This is like a Manhattan/Whiskey Sour remix that you can recreate at home even if you aren’t as strikingly handsome and super talented as Rob is! 😀

Black Rose
1.5 @blackenedamericanwhiskey
.25 Dolin Sweet Vermouth 
.25 Angostura Amaro
1oz Pomegranate Juice
.5 oz fresh lemon juice
.5 oz cane simple syrup (2:1)
1 egg white
Garnish: Angostura Art
Glassware: Footed “V” glass
Directions: Combine all ingredients, dry shake, add 3 cold draft ice cubes and Shake again than Double strain over 3 fresh ice cubes. For this glassware, adjust as needed.

We always love stoping by @oakandivydtlv when we are in Vegas! 🙌 This time we were just driving through but we made sure we stopped in for a cocktail. @makerofdrinks made a few gems for us but this one stood out and gave us some ideas to try at home. This is a “BBQ smoked old fashioned” - the BBQ influence coming from the rub on the rim of the glass and a house-made BBQ bitters. 😍 Needless to say we are going to be working out some @traegergrills riffs on this at home...we’ll keep you posted on the R&D! 🔥
